<TITLE> Teenager shoots himself in Chittagong </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Sept 23 (bdnews24.com)A teenager accidentally shot himself in the head on Wednesday while mimicking action movie stars at Chotteswari Road in Chittagong. Raju Hossain, 17, son of Abu Monsur, who is nephew of late Awami League leader M A Mannan, was playing with his father's licensed pistol when he pulled the trigger at noon. He was admitted to the neurosurgery ward of Chittagong Medical College Hospital in critical condition, sub-inspector Zahurul Haque, who was in charge of CMCH police post, told bdnews24.com quoting Raju's family. Kotowali police chief Mohiuddin Mahmud said the licensed pistol of Raju's father was under the pillow on the bed. He was showing his younger brothers how the action movie stars shoot, said Mohiuddin. Mohiuddin added said police were on the scene for investigation. bdn
